# Backend base URL. MUST include the /api/v1 suffix: api.ts and assistantClient.ts append
# paths straight onto it (`${BASE}/cases`, `${BASE}/assistant/message`), and the WebSocket
# helpers strip the suffix themselves before dialling /ws/... . Without the suffix every
# call 404s.
#
# Leave it UNSET to use vite.config.ts's dev proxy instead (same-origin /api/v1 and /ws,
# forwarded server-side to the hosted backend) -- that is what the committed .env does,
# and it sidesteps AppSail's CORS preflight gap. Set it only to point at a local backend.
#VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:9000/api/v1

# The assistant has exactly one mode: the real backend agent. The scripted demo stream and
# its canned answers were deleted when the LangGraph assistant landed, so there is no
# VITE_ASSISTANT_API flag any more -- every answer is generated live against Postgres,
# Neo4j and Pinecone.
